Conclusion¶

  1. This is an important dataset representing the weather summary over the world war 2 period. Analysis and prediction using this dataset would help in planning milatary operation.
  2. Here we are predicting maximum temperature using linear regression algorithm. Firstly we plotted a correlation matrix for the variables and found that Maximum Temperature had a high correlation (0.88) with minimum temperature. Hence we used minimum temperature as our Key independent variable.
  3. After application of Linear regression algorithm, we predicted maximum temprature with an root means square of 11.396. 4.To further improve the model, we applied cube root transformation as our data was left skewed. After applying the linear regression algorithm on transformed data we reduced the Root mean square error to 1.017
